1
00:01:29,039 --> 00:01:32,009
[Silent Honor]

2
00:01:32,370 --> 00:01:34,860
[Episode 13]

3
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:17,280
From November 1st, 1949

4
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:19,020
to December 27th, 1949,

5
00:02:19,780 --> 00:02:22,240
the PLA spent 57 days

6
00:02:22,590 --> 00:02:26,780
liberating most parts of Sichuan, Xikang,
Yunnan and Guizhou,

7
00:02:27,150 --> 00:02:29,690
as well as over 500 cities and towns

8
00:02:29,740 --> 00:02:31,740
in Hunan, Hubei, Shaanxi and Gansu.

9
00:02:32,340 --> 00:02:34,170
Chiang Kai-shek personally
directed the battles,

10
00:02:34,170 --> 00:02:36,570
yet he could not reverse
the tide of defeat.

11
00:02:36,660 --> 00:02:38,070
On December 10th,

12
00:02:38,180 --> 00:02:40,079
he flew from Chengdu to Taiwan,

13
00:02:40,579 --> 00:02:44,120
and never set foot
on the Chinese mainland again.

14
00:02:42,040 --> 00:02:46,660
[Caoshan Villa]

15
00:02:46,750 --> 00:02:47,500
President.

16
00:02:48,190 --> 00:02:51,450
These are several plans
from the Ministry of Defense about

17
00:02:51,490 --> 00:02:54,470
recapturing Kunming
and punishing the traitor Lu Han,

18
00:02:54,470 --> 00:02:57,740
including deploying troops
from nearby areas to close in on Kunming

19
00:02:57,740 --> 00:02:59,740
and carrying out
a direct air force bombing

20
00:02:59,740 --> 00:03:02,580
on Wuhua Mountain
where the Yunnan Provincial Government is.

21
00:03:02,580 --> 00:03:05,040
It seems everyone
at the Ministry of Defense

22
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:07,760
is filled with righteous indignation.

23
00:03:08,580 --> 00:03:10,410
We're just waiting for your order,
President.

24
00:03:10,410 --> 00:03:11,060
No hurry.

25
00:03:18,940 --> 00:03:19,850
Zhirou.

26
00:03:20,780 --> 00:03:22,530
To suppress the rebellion
and save the nation,

27
00:03:22,530 --> 00:03:25,230
punishing Lu Han alone
is far from enough.

28
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:30,180
I have more important arrangements
for the air force.

29
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:33,240
Yes, sir.

30
00:03:35,250 --> 00:03:36,980
We lost the Southwest Campaign

31
00:03:37,180 --> 00:03:39,860
and there is the deciphered content
of the telegram.

32
00:03:39,860 --> 00:03:43,190
I suspect there's a Communist spy
in the military top brass.

33
00:03:45,060 --> 00:03:47,570
Where is Gu Zhengwen now?

34
00:03:48,590 --> 00:04:02,100
[BIS of the Ministry of Defense]

35
00:03:58,100 --> 00:03:58,829
Director.

36
00:03:59,460 --> 00:04:01,630
The terrain in Taichung's
mountainous areas is complex.

37
00:04:01,630 --> 00:04:04,030
And inter-village transportation
is often inconvenient.

38
00:04:04,030 --> 00:04:06,410
Posing as a school teacher,

39
00:04:06,560 --> 00:04:08,970
I built closer relations
with local villagers.

40
00:04:08,970 --> 00:04:10,840
Through extensive investigations,

41
00:04:10,840 --> 00:04:11,800
it wasn't until recently

42
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:14,020
that I discovered that a group of people,

43
00:04:14,020 --> 00:04:16,120
under the pretext of land reclamation,

44
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:17,300
were engaging in large-scale purchases

45
00:04:17,300 --> 00:04:18,950
of weapons left behind
by the Japanese army.

46
00:04:18,950 --> 00:04:22,420
Combined with the previously collected
information,

47
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:24,450
I think that

48
00:04:24,450 --> 00:04:26,950
one of armed bases
of the Communist spies

49
00:04:26,950 --> 00:04:30,800
is likely located in the area
between Zhuzikeng and Baimao Mountain.

50
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:31,920
As for the exact location,

51
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:34,540
we still need
further detailed investigations.

52
00:04:34,540 --> 00:04:36,310
You go compile this into a document.

53
00:04:36,310 --> 00:04:38,070
I'll send others
to conduct the investigation.

54
00:04:38,070 --> 00:04:38,600
Yes, sir.

55
00:04:39,650 --> 00:04:42,980
Now that the Nationalist Army
keeps retreating in defeat,

56
00:04:43,630 --> 00:04:45,450
intelligence personnel
from all over the country

57
00:04:45,450 --> 00:04:47,060
have come to Taiwan.

58
00:04:47,909 --> 00:04:48,820
But in Taiwan,

59
00:04:50,820 --> 00:04:53,010
there can't be
too many Communist spies.

60
00:04:53,010 --> 00:04:54,610
We don't need so many people.

61
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:58,740
So rectification and downsizing
are imperative.

62
00:04:59,810 --> 00:05:03,010
Only those who deliver results
get to keep their positions.

63
00:05:03,010 --> 00:05:03,690
Yes, sir.

64
00:05:04,510 --> 00:05:06,120
We've almost run out of the credit we got

65
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:08,450
from our success
with the Guangming News case.

66
00:05:08,450 --> 00:05:10,920
It's time to reopen the Zhang Hao case.

67
00:05:11,950 --> 00:05:12,480
Yes, sir.

68
00:05:12,950 --> 00:05:13,450
Well,

69
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:16,100
your last trip to Hong Kong
wasn't in vain.

70
00:05:16,100 --> 00:05:17,560
Using the key and codebook

71
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:18,570
you brought back,

72
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:22,320
the Section 4 deciphered a telegram
that was intercepted

73
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:23,740
on September 21st.

74
00:05:23,950 --> 00:05:27,020
It contained military deployments
for Kinmen and Xiamen.

75
00:05:27,020 --> 00:05:29,400
And according to Liu Kangfu's confession,

76
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:30,930
he was sending the telegram

77
00:05:31,010 --> 00:05:33,540
to a Communist spy team called East Sea.

78
00:05:33,540 --> 00:05:35,930
So I suspect that the East Sea

79
00:05:35,930 --> 00:05:38,530
is hiding within the upper echelons
of the Nationalist Government.

80
00:05:38,530 --> 00:05:40,470
Comrade Jianfeng has agreed

81
00:05:41,280 --> 00:05:42,470
that from now on,

82
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:45,390
you'll be reinstated
to your original position.

83
00:05:45,390 --> 00:05:48,920
Go find out that Communist spy.

84
00:05:49,300 --> 00:05:49,940
Yes, sir!

85
00:05:50,580 --> 00:05:51,760
Captain Liu.

86
00:05:52,570 --> 00:05:53,970
The numbers don't add up.

87
00:05:54,490 --> 00:05:55,880
It's short by about 100 kg.

88
00:05:55,880 --> 00:05:57,010
That can't be right.

89
00:05:57,370 --> 00:05:58,570
Did you count wrong?

90
00:05:58,600 --> 00:06:00,460
How could I possibly count wrong?

91
00:06:01,750 --> 00:06:02,570
Captain Liu.

92
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:05,560
You can't keep giving us less each month.

93
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:07,020
That's not proper, right?

94
00:06:07,220 --> 00:06:08,440
There're so many men in my team.

95
00:06:08,440 --> 00:06:10,500
How am I supposed
to distribute this?

96
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:12,500
I'm just the delivery man.

97
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:15,440
I deliver exactly
what is allocated to you.

98
00:06:15,740 --> 00:06:17,800
We're colleagues working together.

99
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:19,850
I wouldn't cut your food short,

100
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:20,800
would I?

101
00:06:21,500 --> 00:06:22,000
I'm off.

102
00:06:22,430 --> 00:06:23,160
Captain Liu!

103
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:26,540
The numbers just don't add up.

104
00:06:26,540 --> 00:06:27,600
What do you mean?

105
00:06:27,930 --> 00:06:28,880
If you're not satisfied,

106
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:29,950
I'll just take it all back.

107
00:06:29,950 --> 00:06:31,270
I can just send someone else
to drop it off,

108
00:06:31,270 --> 00:06:32,760
and it'll end up another 100 kg short.

109
00:06:32,760 --> 00:06:34,250
It's not about my satisfaction.

110
00:06:34,250 --> 00:06:35,130
There are so many people in my team.

111
00:06:35,130 --> 00:06:36,390
We can let everyone see

112
00:06:36,550 --> 00:06:38,480
if it gets less and less each month.

113
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:39,690
I'm not lying to you!

114
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:40,640
Lianwang.

115
00:06:41,310 --> 00:06:42,770
Come here and be the judge.

116
00:06:42,950 --> 00:06:44,480
Lianwang, come take a look.

117
00:06:44,540 --> 00:06:46,000
See if they're skimming off
the army rations.

118
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,060
I don't really understand
these things.

119
00:06:47,060 --> 00:06:48,800
How can you not understand this?
Come here.

120
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:49,300
You...

121
00:06:50,350 --> 00:06:51,420
I left my folder inside.

122
00:06:51,420 --> 00:06:51,740
I forgot to bring my folder.

123
00:06:51,740 --> 00:06:52,360
Lianwang.

124
00:06:52,710 --> 00:06:53,390
See?

125
00:06:54,430 --> 00:06:56,430
Nobody wants to get involved.

126
00:06:56,750 --> 00:06:57,740
In the army, it's always the superiors

127
00:06:57,740 --> 00:06:58,750
that take advantage
of the ones below them.

128
00:06:58,750 --> 00:06:59,480
Captain Liu.

129
00:07:00,100 --> 00:07:02,110
If you don't make up the shortage today,

130
00:07:02,110 --> 00:07:03,680
you don't even think about leaving.

131
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:04,780
Are you asking for trouble?

132
00:07:04,780 --> 00:07:05,970
Yes, I am asking for trouble.

133
00:07:05,970 --> 00:07:06,610
You!

134
00:07:07,650 --> 00:07:09,060
Stop, stop, stop!

135
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:12,680
Leader!

136
00:07:13,980 --> 00:07:15,640
You're finally back, Leader.

137
00:07:15,750 --> 00:07:16,750
They've been holding back
our food supplies.

138
00:07:16,750 --> 00:07:17,250
Nonsense!

139
00:07:17,250 --> 00:07:18,980
Holding back the army rations?

140
00:07:19,310 --> 00:07:19,900
Mr. Gu.

141
00:07:20,020 --> 00:07:21,630
Captain Liu, that's impossible, right?

142
00:07:21,630 --> 00:07:22,450
Mr. Gu.

143
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:26,530
We both work
for the Nationalist Government.

144
00:07:27,130 --> 00:07:29,540
Times are tough for everyone now.

145
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:30,720
I understand that.

146
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:32,530
It's not easy, but that's okay.

147
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:33,810
I'm back now.

148
00:07:36,220 --> 00:07:36,820
By the way,

149
00:07:38,990 --> 00:07:41,340
here's some money,
which is not much to share.

150
00:07:41,340 --> 00:07:43,670
Take it and get everyone something to eat.

151
00:07:47,940 --> 00:07:48,670
Captain Liu.

152
00:07:49,060 --> 00:07:51,320
If there's really not enough food
for us,

153
00:07:51,670 --> 00:07:53,110
just take all this away.

154
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:54,480
That won't be necessary, Mr. Gu.

155
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:54,980
No need.

156
00:07:54,980 --> 00:07:55,510
I mean it.

157
00:07:56,570 --> 00:07:57,830
When there's a proper opportunity later,

158
00:07:57,830 --> 00:07:59,590
I'll get more for you to make up for it.

159
00:07:59,590 --> 00:07:59,990
Really?

160
00:07:59,990 --> 00:08:00,630
Yes.

161
00:08:00,740 --> 00:08:01,500
Thank you.

162
00:08:02,100 --> 00:08:03,160
Thank you.

163
00:08:07,140 --> 00:08:07,830
Leader.

164
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:11,540
I thank you on behalf of everyone.

165
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:13,250
You've finally returned.

166
00:08:13,250 --> 00:08:14,750
You don't know when you were gone...

167
00:08:14,750 --> 00:08:17,070
Enough. Don't dwell
on these small matters.

168
00:08:17,070 --> 00:08:18,570
Get me the schedule number

169
00:08:18,570 --> 00:08:20,300
for the Ping'an Ship. I need it.

170
00:08:21,180 --> 00:08:22,980
Help me take the stuff upstairs.

171
00:08:25,100 --> 00:08:26,060
Be careful!

172
00:08:26,280 --> 00:08:26,940
-Yes.
-Yes.

173
00:08:31,450 --> 00:08:31,910
Leader.

174
00:08:36,610 --> 00:08:38,000
I'm going to read the newspaper.

175
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:40,400
I'm going to read the newspaper
for a while.

176
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:41,549
Be good.

177
00:09:00,590 --> 00:09:06,340
[Communist Party Members' Remains
Were Found on Coast After Over Ten Days]

178
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:33,920
At 10 PM on September 19th,

179
00:09:34,620 --> 00:09:36,280
it arrived at Keelung Harbor.

180
00:09:36,650 --> 00:09:38,310
It departed at 6 AM on the 21st.

181
00:09:38,860 --> 00:09:40,240
Leader, I found it.

182
00:09:44,130 --> 00:09:45,010
So Zhang Hao

183
00:09:46,940 --> 00:09:48,030
sent the telegram right after

184
00:09:48,030 --> 00:09:49,700
the ship departed on the 21st.

185
00:09:51,390 --> 00:09:53,680
But at 10 PM on the 19th,

186
00:09:53,710 --> 00:09:55,310
the ship arrived in Keelung.

187
00:09:56,220 --> 00:09:58,350
Keelung was under curfew at that time.

188
00:09:59,270 --> 00:10:00,320
That means

189
00:10:00,910 --> 00:10:03,440
he could only get the content
for the telegram

190
00:10:04,170 --> 00:10:05,900
during the daytime of the 20th.

191
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:06,980
What telegram?

192
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:17,690
It has been deciphered!

193
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:21,240
Take Liu Kangfu
to the interrogation room.

194
00:10:23,700 --> 00:10:25,890
Do you know why you're here?

195
00:10:26,650 --> 00:10:27,910
I previously

196
00:10:28,270 --> 00:10:29,700
ruined your big plan.

197
00:10:31,490 --> 00:10:34,330
And now this is my chance
to atone for my mistakes.

198
00:10:35,650 --> 00:10:37,030
It's not some big plan.

199
00:10:37,170 --> 00:10:38,930
Things are always changing.

200
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:40,930
It's not all your fault.

201
00:10:42,170 --> 00:10:44,300
This time your mission is very simple.

202
00:10:45,030 --> 00:10:46,150
You just need to

203
00:10:47,170 --> 00:10:48,740
tell me every single detail

204
00:10:48,740 --> 00:10:50,250
about Zhang Hao and you

205
00:10:51,170 --> 00:10:52,670
since you met,

206
00:10:53,630 --> 00:10:54,960
including what he said,

207
00:10:55,310 --> 00:10:56,650
what he did,

208
00:10:57,370 --> 00:10:59,620
even what clothes he wore,

209
00:10:59,620 --> 00:11:02,320
and his habitual phrases

210
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:03,220
and gestures.

211
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:05,530
Tell me everything in detail.

212
00:11:05,910 --> 00:11:07,410
Okay, I'll tell you.

213
00:11:07,410 --> 00:11:08,870
I'll tell you everything.

214
00:11:10,150 --> 00:11:12,580
I first met Zhang Hao

215
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:14,670
at the end of August.

216
00:11:15,740 --> 00:11:17,130
At that time, I had been assigned to work

217
00:11:17,130 --> 00:11:18,370
on the Ping'an Ship
by the Taiwan Work Committee

218
00:11:18,370 --> 00:11:19,770
for more than two months.

219
00:11:20,630 --> 00:11:21,890
He was the first mate on the ship.

220
00:11:21,890 --> 00:11:22,340
Right.

221
00:11:23,100 --> 00:11:25,830
I was practicing
throwing mooring lines that day

222
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:27,860
when he suddenly came up to me.

223
00:11:30,250 --> 00:11:31,180
Deputy Chief Wu.

224
00:11:35,030 --> 00:11:35,960
Deputy Chief Wu.

225
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:41,030
The Chief hasn't returned yet?

226
00:11:41,030 --> 00:11:41,840
Not yet.

227
00:11:42,740 --> 00:11:44,270
There's no meeting
at the ministry today.

228
00:11:44,270 --> 00:11:45,530
Where did he go for a meeting?

229
00:11:45,530 --> 00:11:47,740
I'm not quite sure about the details.

230
00:11:48,270 --> 00:11:50,670
How about I call you
when the Chief returns?

231
00:11:50,770 --> 00:11:52,120
You're the First Secretary.

232
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:53,180
And you don't know?

233
00:11:53,980 --> 00:11:56,100
General Huang Jie has sent
three urgent telegrams in one day.

234
00:11:56,100 --> 00:11:57,940
I'm waiting for the Chief's decision.

235
00:11:57,940 --> 00:11:58,620
Well...

236
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:02,880
The Chief went to the Hsinchu base
for a meeting.

237
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:06,250
He specifically ordered
that no one should disturb him.

238
00:12:06,970 --> 00:12:07,540
Fine.

239
00:12:08,010 --> 00:12:09,810
Let me know as soon as he returns.

240
00:12:09,820 --> 00:12:10,360
Yes, sir!

241
00:12:12,270 --> 00:12:14,740
September 20th?

242
00:12:17,110 --> 00:12:18,680
The question is so sudden

243
00:12:18,740 --> 00:12:20,200
that I can't remember now.

244
00:12:20,390 --> 00:12:22,050
It has been over three months.

245
00:12:26,130 --> 00:12:26,910
It has indeed been

246
00:12:26,910 --> 00:12:27,970
over three months.

247
00:12:30,460 --> 00:12:31,530
But look,

248
00:12:32,150 --> 00:12:35,560
the Ping'an Ship arrived at Keelung Harbor

249
00:12:35,590 --> 00:12:37,050
on the evening of the 19th.

250
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:40,620
But in the early morning of the 21st,

251
00:12:40,640 --> 00:12:42,790
it left Keelung Harbor for Guangzhou.

252
00:12:42,820 --> 00:12:44,530
That means Zhang Hao

253
00:12:45,910 --> 00:12:48,000
could only have gone to Taipei

254
00:12:48,030 --> 00:12:50,120
during the day on the 20th.

255
00:12:50,340 --> 00:12:52,340
Now that you mention it, I remember.

256
00:12:53,010 --> 00:12:55,140
That docking was particularly hasty.

257
00:12:55,150 --> 00:12:57,610
We weren't allowed
to get off the ship at all.

258
00:12:57,910 --> 00:12:59,640
As for whether Zhang Hao got off

259
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:01,200
or where he went,

260
00:13:01,940 --> 00:13:03,120
I have no idea.

261
00:13:03,760 --> 00:13:04,540
Mr. Gu,

262
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:07,120
I've only met Zhang Hao

263
00:13:07,650 --> 00:13:08,910
a few times in total.

264
00:13:09,520 --> 00:13:11,240
I've already told you everything I know

265
00:13:11,240 --> 00:13:12,860
and I can remember.

266
00:13:15,290 --> 00:13:16,090
I believe you.

267
00:13:33,530 --> 00:13:35,320
Was there any informal contact

268
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:37,870
between Zhang Hao and you

269
00:13:38,500 --> 00:13:40,030
that was not related to your party work

270
00:13:40,030 --> 00:13:42,440
or your duties on the Ping'an Ship?

271
00:13:44,490 --> 00:13:47,290
Now that you mention it,
there was indeed one time.

272
00:13:47,930 --> 00:13:49,570
When I was eating
at a restaurant in Keelung,

273
00:13:49,570 --> 00:13:50,700
I ran into Zhang Hao.

274
00:13:51,620 --> 00:13:52,480
When was this?

275
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:53,670
Who did he meet?

276
00:13:53,740 --> 00:13:54,670
Did he see you?

277
00:13:56,080 --> 00:13:58,280
It was probably also in late September.

278
00:13:59,340 --> 00:14:01,670
I really don't remember what he was doing.

279
00:14:01,780 --> 00:14:03,580
I was sitting in the restaurant.

280
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,460
He probably didn't see me.

281
00:14:07,920 --> 00:14:09,870
It was very hot that day.

282
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:12,150
There were a lot of salted fish
drying on the street,

283
00:14:12,150 --> 00:14:13,880
with a fishy smell everywhere.

284
00:14:16,390 --> 00:14:17,410
What did you eat?

285
00:14:18,940 --> 00:14:19,960
Sanxian Noodles.

286
00:14:23,680 --> 00:14:24,280
Sir.

287
00:14:24,770 --> 00:14:26,240
You think there's something wrong
with Zhou Zhirou

288
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:28,240
rushing to Hsinchu for the meeting?

289
00:14:29,590 --> 00:14:30,940
It's definitely unusual.

290
00:14:30,940 --> 00:14:31,800
It seems that

291
00:14:31,830 --> 00:14:33,830
the air force will take action soon.

292
00:14:34,860 --> 00:14:35,860
That's possible.

293
00:14:37,260 --> 00:14:38,000
Mr. Chiang

294
00:14:38,290 --> 00:14:40,290
is furious about Lu Han's uprising.

295
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:43,890
Is the air force planning to retaliate
against Lu Han

296
00:14:43,890 --> 00:14:45,020
by bombing Kunming?

297
00:14:45,260 --> 00:14:47,620
Or will they send the air force

298
00:14:47,930 --> 00:14:50,330
to support Hu Zongnan
at the Chengdu front?

299
00:14:54,390 --> 00:14:55,320
China is so vast.

300
00:14:55,770 --> 00:14:58,900
We can't rule out that Mr. Chiang
might have other plans.

301
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:08,790
Mr. Gu, aren't you eating?

302
00:15:09,830 --> 00:15:11,760
Never mind. I'm not hungry anyway.

303
00:15:13,370 --> 00:15:14,230
It tastes good?

304
00:15:14,430 --> 00:15:15,050
It's fine.

305
00:15:17,530 --> 00:15:18,130
Both taste

306
00:15:18,890 --> 00:15:19,630
and smell

307
00:15:20,100 --> 00:15:21,530
can help you remember.

308
00:15:22,050 --> 00:15:23,710
Have you thought of anything?

309
00:15:25,510 --> 00:15:26,100
No.

310
00:15:33,150 --> 00:15:33,980
That's okay.

311
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:36,100
Well then...

312
00:15:36,650 --> 00:15:39,030
When you saw Zhang Hao that day,

313
00:15:39,030 --> 00:15:40,980
was he right in front of you

314
00:15:40,980 --> 00:15:42,100
or was he on your

315
00:15:43,080 --> 00:15:43,650
left

316
00:15:43,940 --> 00:15:44,510
or right?

317
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:45,670
Right.

318
00:15:46,770 --> 00:15:47,570
On your right?

319
00:15:48,530 --> 00:15:49,440
On your right.

320
00:15:50,290 --> 00:15:51,070
On your left?

321
00:15:51,100 --> 00:15:51,700
This side.

322
00:15:53,940 --> 00:15:55,270
On your left.

323
00:15:56,500 --> 00:15:59,740
You were eating Sanxian Noodles that day.

324
00:16:00,240 --> 00:16:01,890
You turned your head to the left

325
00:16:01,890 --> 00:16:03,670
and saw Zhang Hao.

326
00:16:04,630 --> 00:16:05,290
Xiaonan.

327
00:16:06,410 --> 00:16:07,010
Come here.

328
00:16:07,890 --> 00:16:08,750
Stand here.

329
00:16:09,340 --> 00:16:10,140
Hurry.

330
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:13,120
You play Zhang Hao. Here.

331
00:16:15,670 --> 00:16:18,290
Was Zhang Hao talking with...

332
00:16:20,150 --> 00:16:20,840
Yes.

333
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:24,740
So Zhang Hao was talking to someone

334
00:16:24,740 --> 00:16:26,360
and you couldn't see that person

335
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:27,960
due to this position, right?

336
00:16:27,980 --> 00:16:29,780
That person was behind the wall.

337
00:16:32,140 --> 00:16:33,510
There was a wall on this side?

338
00:16:33,510 --> 00:16:33,890
Yes.

339
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:36,960
No wonder.

340
00:16:38,550 --> 00:16:39,280
Turn around.

341
00:16:39,950 --> 00:16:41,340
-Turn around.
-Yeah.

342
00:16:41,370 --> 00:16:43,410
Right. Zhang Hao turned around,

343
00:16:43,410 --> 00:16:44,740
and that's how I saw him.

344
00:16:45,120 --> 00:16:46,270
I remember that day

345
00:16:47,250 --> 00:16:49,500
he seemed reluctant to leave.

346
00:16:54,340 --> 00:16:55,670
Reluctant to leave?

347
00:17:02,650 --> 00:17:03,650
Well, it seems

348
00:17:05,170 --> 00:17:06,630
the person behind the wall

349
00:17:07,270 --> 00:17:09,670
had a special relationship with Zhang Hao.

350
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:12,829
I'll take you to Keelung Harbor tomorrow.

351
00:17:41,470 --> 00:17:42,160
Wait.

352
00:17:43,220 --> 00:17:44,220
I think it's here.

353
00:17:44,640 --> 00:17:45,300
Don't stop now.

354
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:47,030
Find a place to pull over ahead.

355
00:17:52,230 --> 00:17:54,950
I remember it was around here.

356
00:17:55,680 --> 00:17:57,270
There were many snack stands

357
00:17:57,270 --> 00:17:58,400
in this area.

358
00:18:03,660 --> 00:18:04,200
Here.

359
00:18:04,750 --> 00:18:05,330
This way.

360
00:18:07,190 --> 00:18:09,140
I was sitting right in this spot

361
00:18:09,440 --> 00:18:11,170
and he was standing over there.

362
00:18:16,940 --> 00:18:18,340
Isn't this on your right?

363
00:18:19,330 --> 00:18:20,960
Sorry, I made a mistake.

364
00:18:24,140 --> 00:18:26,050
So you were looking

365
00:18:26,950 --> 00:18:28,210
at that direction?

366
00:18:28,850 --> 00:18:29,640
Yes.

367
00:18:29,790 --> 00:18:30,570
Are you sure?

368
00:18:31,440 --> 00:18:32,840
Definitely. Right here.

369
00:18:52,290 --> 00:18:54,410
Let me know if you have dried oysters.

370
00:18:55,930 --> 00:18:56,900
Hold this.

371
00:18:56,930 --> 00:18:57,870
Thank you.

372
00:19:01,030 --> 00:19:01,700
Hello.

373
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:02,720
Hello.

374
00:19:02,890 --> 00:19:04,870
What kind of fish is this?

375
00:19:05,420 --> 00:19:06,500
It's the local Sipo fish,

376
00:19:06,500 --> 00:19:07,630
also called Balang.

377
00:19:07,850 --> 00:19:10,380
It adds great flavor to congee and soup.

378
00:19:11,180 --> 00:19:12,510
I was worried
you couldn't understand what I said.

379
00:19:12,510 --> 00:19:13,970
Are you not a local either?

380
00:19:15,220 --> 00:19:16,480
In business, customers come

381
00:19:16,480 --> 00:19:17,810
from all over the world.

382
00:19:17,960 --> 00:19:20,570
Learning some local dialect
helps with business, right?

383
00:19:20,570 --> 00:19:21,250
Yes, indeed.

384
00:19:21,250 --> 00:19:22,540
I'll take some of this.

385
00:19:22,570 --> 00:19:23,080
Sure.

386
00:19:23,630 --> 00:19:24,380
These are good.

387
00:19:24,380 --> 00:19:25,780
Let me weigh some for you.

388
00:19:25,790 --> 00:19:26,640
Great.

389
00:19:28,720 --> 00:19:29,380
Leader,

390
00:19:29,440 --> 00:19:32,370
do you think there's something wrong
with this shop?

391
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:39,330
Why isn't Mrs. Ma here today?

392
00:19:39,510 --> 00:19:41,250
She loves playing mahjong the most,
doesn't she?

393
00:19:41,250 --> 00:19:43,380
Director Ma has got another mistress.

394
00:19:43,470 --> 00:19:47,130
Director Ma is such a playboy.
He changes mistresses every month.

395
00:19:49,050 --> 00:19:49,900
You really don't want to know

396
00:19:49,900 --> 00:19:51,090
who that woman is?

397
00:19:51,330 --> 00:19:52,070
Who is she?

398
00:19:52,440 --> 00:19:54,160
The the lead songstress at Huadu Ballroom.

399
00:19:54,160 --> 00:19:55,820
She's also an air force widow.

400
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:58,250
She was a college student.

401
00:19:58,250 --> 00:20:00,010
After graduation, she married a pilot.

402
00:20:00,010 --> 00:20:01,250
The day after their wedding,

403
00:20:01,250 --> 00:20:03,360
her husband's plane
fell from the sky.

404
00:20:03,360 --> 00:20:05,220
She came to Taiwan
and became a songstress.

405
00:20:05,220 --> 00:20:06,140
I've seen her.

406
00:20:06,350 --> 00:20:08,010
She's incredibly beautiful.

407
00:20:08,770 --> 00:20:10,510
No wonder Director Ma can't resist her

408
00:20:10,510 --> 00:20:11,720
and never goes home.

409
00:20:12,070 --> 00:20:14,330
Mrs. Huang, would you play for me
for a while?

410
00:20:14,330 --> 00:20:15,550
I suddenly got a headache.

411
00:20:15,550 --> 00:20:16,880
I'll go rest over there.

412
00:20:16,880 --> 00:20:18,340
All right, I'll take over.

413
00:20:20,810 --> 00:20:23,520
Where do you pick up
all these gossipy bits?

414
00:20:24,140 --> 00:20:25,980
My husband told me!

415
00:20:28,120 --> 00:20:29,790
His job is basically gathering information

416
00:20:29,790 --> 00:20:31,440
about others, isn't it?

417
00:20:31,740 --> 00:20:32,550
Your husband knows

418
00:20:32,550 --> 00:20:33,960
so much gossip.

419
00:20:33,960 --> 00:20:35,080
Aren't you afraid he might

420
00:20:35,080 --> 00:20:37,210
follow Director Ma to Huadu Ballroom?

421
00:20:38,090 --> 00:20:39,250
If he really wants to do that,

422
00:20:39,250 --> 00:20:40,780
how can I possibly stop him?

423
00:20:41,130 --> 00:20:42,590
As long as he doesn't bring
his mistress home, it's fine.

424
00:20:42,590 --> 00:20:43,920
You're so open-minded.

425
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:45,700
What else can I do?

426
00:20:47,110 --> 00:20:47,960
That's true.

427
00:20:47,960 --> 00:20:49,350
You can't exactly

428
00:20:49,350 --> 00:20:51,210
tie your husband down with a rope.

429
00:20:52,900 --> 00:20:54,400
Mrs. Wu, I really envy you.

430
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:55,960
You never have to worry about such things,

431
00:20:55,960 --> 00:20:56,490
right?

432
00:20:57,450 --> 00:20:59,030
My husband also said

433
00:20:59,060 --> 00:21:00,930
that Deputy Chief Wu is a really good man,

434
00:21:00,930 --> 00:21:02,740
who never flirts with other women

435
00:21:02,740 --> 00:21:04,340
and only focuses on his work.

436
00:21:04,350 --> 00:21:05,040
Exactly.

437
00:21:05,070 --> 00:21:06,200
I've heard that too.

438
00:21:09,620 --> 00:21:11,820
You can't judge people by appearances.

439
00:21:12,240 --> 00:21:13,400
I've heard that

440
00:21:13,610 --> 00:21:15,640
a woman went
to Power Company Guesthouse

441
00:21:15,640 --> 00:21:16,900
to see Deputy Chief Wu.

442
00:21:17,270 --> 00:21:17,810
Keep your voice down.

443
00:21:17,810 --> 00:21:19,310
Your husband is really something,

444
00:21:19,310 --> 00:21:21,770
spying even
on his superior's personal life.

445
00:21:21,770 --> 00:21:23,010
Deputy Chief Wu?

446
00:21:23,040 --> 00:21:24,480
Didn't he just move?

447
00:21:24,710 --> 00:21:27,570
Could it have been a female colleague
or something?

448
00:21:28,170 --> 00:21:29,700
She was dressed like a rich madam,

449
00:21:29,700 --> 00:21:30,980
so she definitely is not a colleague.

450
00:21:30,980 --> 00:21:31,680
Enough.

451
00:21:31,710 --> 00:21:33,830
Stop gossiping behind people's backs.

452
00:21:33,830 --> 00:21:34,680
Mrs. Dou.

453
00:21:35,350 --> 00:21:36,110
I'm really sorry,

454
00:21:36,110 --> 00:21:37,750
but I'm just too tired.

455
00:21:37,930 --> 00:21:39,230
I'll leave first, okay?

456
00:21:39,230 --> 00:21:40,600
Please enjoy yourselves.

457
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:41,440
Goodbye, Mrs. Wu.

458
00:21:41,440 --> 00:21:42,210
See you next time.

459
00:21:42,210 --> 00:21:43,050
Alright, goodbye.

460
00:21:43,050 --> 00:21:43,880
-Goodbye.
-Goodbye.

461
00:21:43,880 --> 00:21:45,590
Liu, bring Mrs. Wu's shawl over here.

462
00:21:45,590 --> 00:21:46,550
Coming.

463
00:21:46,660 --> 00:21:47,720
Here. Give it to me.

464
00:21:48,120 --> 00:21:49,080
Thank you.

465
00:21:50,020 --> 00:21:51,290
I'm sorry about today.

466
00:21:51,710 --> 00:21:53,370
I've ruined everyone's mood.

467
00:21:54,190 --> 00:21:55,070
Not at all.

468
00:21:55,070 --> 00:21:56,720
You're always welcome here.

469
00:21:57,990 --> 00:21:58,770
It's my fault.

470
00:21:58,770 --> 00:22:00,480
I should invite just anyone to my home.

471
00:22:00,480 --> 00:22:01,180
It's fine.

472
00:22:01,180 --> 00:22:02,110
Go back inside.

473
00:22:02,680 --> 00:22:03,400
Goodbye.

474
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:27,330
She's angry with me?

475
00:22:28,640 --> 00:22:30,160
Did I say something wrong?

476
00:22:30,590 --> 00:22:31,550
Liu,

477
00:22:31,830 --> 00:22:33,700
bring Mrs. Duan's coat over here.

478
00:22:34,540 --> 00:22:36,000
She should be leaving too.

479
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:38,730
I'm a straightforward person.

480
00:22:38,740 --> 00:22:40,150
I hate gossip the most.

481
00:22:40,480 --> 00:22:42,740
You're no longer welcome at Dou's Mansion.

482
00:22:42,740 --> 00:22:43,540
Please leave.

483
00:22:45,530 --> 00:22:46,990
How could you be like this?

484
00:22:48,030 --> 00:22:49,330
Why is it so hard

485
00:22:49,330 --> 00:22:50,930
to tell the truth these days?

486
00:22:52,370 --> 00:22:54,720
When your husband becomes

487
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:57,130
Deputy Chief Duan, then we'll talk.

488
00:23:01,210 --> 00:23:02,340
Madam, you're back.

489
00:23:28,200 --> 00:23:29,920
Didn't you go to Dou's Mansion
to play mahjong?

490
00:23:29,920 --> 00:23:31,420
Why are you back so early?

491
00:23:32,920 --> 00:23:34,720
You didn't work overtime today?

492
00:23:37,310 --> 00:23:39,250
No. We've made that agreement, haven't we?

493
00:23:39,250 --> 00:23:40,710
I should come home on time.

494
00:23:42,250 --> 00:23:43,670
Nice talk.

495
00:23:45,510 --> 00:23:46,550
I'd rather believe pigs can fly

496
00:23:46,550 --> 00:23:48,410
than believe a man's smooth talk.

497
00:24:00,640 --> 00:24:01,440
What's wrong?

498
00:24:07,810 --> 00:24:10,250
Did you hear something
at Dou's Mansion?

499
00:24:14,480 --> 00:24:16,070
All these years you've worked
so hard outside.

500
00:24:16,070 --> 00:24:17,800
I know that and understand you.

501
00:24:19,960 --> 00:24:22,090
For a high-ranking official like you,

502
00:24:22,950 --> 00:24:25,250
it's normal to have a mistress.

503
00:24:27,310 --> 00:24:28,840
But I only have one request.

504
00:24:30,200 --> 00:24:31,060
Don't lie to me.

505
00:24:35,240 --> 00:24:37,570
Did you hear something from those madams?

506
00:24:38,720 --> 00:24:39,720
What did they say?

507
00:24:40,570 --> 00:24:41,680
Mrs. Ma wasn't there today.

508
00:24:41,680 --> 00:24:42,680
And they said that

509
00:24:43,850 --> 00:24:46,090
Director Ma got another mistress.

510
00:24:47,430 --> 00:24:50,170
Then Mrs. Dou said she envied me.

511
00:24:50,740 --> 00:24:52,590
But Mrs. Duan sitting nearby

512
00:24:54,420 --> 00:24:55,910
started to stir things up,

513
00:24:57,220 --> 00:24:58,960
saying something ridiculous.

514
00:24:59,790 --> 00:25:00,550
Which madam?

515
00:25:02,660 --> 00:25:03,530
Mrs. Duan.

516
00:25:06,300 --> 00:25:07,930
What ridiculous things did she say?

517
00:25:07,930 --> 00:25:09,030
Don't ask anymore.

518
00:25:10,070 --> 00:25:10,990
It was nothing.

519
00:25:12,720 --> 00:25:13,500
Yuxun.

520
00:25:17,070 --> 00:25:18,180
I only have one request.

521
00:25:18,180 --> 00:25:19,180
No matter what,

522
00:25:19,790 --> 00:25:21,180
don't lie to me.

523
00:25:23,420 --> 00:25:24,100
Bikui.

524
00:25:27,070 --> 00:25:29,940
We met and fell in love when you were 18.

525
00:25:32,330 --> 00:25:34,130
We've been married for 30 years.

526
00:25:36,070 --> 00:25:37,130
Doesn't all of this

527
00:25:37,970 --> 00:25:40,120
outweigh their gossip?

528
00:25:42,340 --> 00:25:44,270
I shouldn't have listened to them.

529
00:25:46,450 --> 00:25:47,980
I shouldn't have listened.

530
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:49,520
It was nonsense.

531
00:25:50,420 --> 00:25:51,420
Come on, Bikui.

532
00:25:52,350 --> 00:25:53,750
Listen to this.

533
00:25:56,900 --> 00:25:58,230
No matter what you hear,

534
00:25:59,700 --> 00:26:00,890
you must believe

535
00:26:02,530 --> 00:26:03,660
I won't lie to you.

536
00:26:06,010 --> 00:26:06,980
Trust me.

537
00:26:18,220 --> 00:26:20,080
Your hairstyle looks beautiful.

538
00:26:47,550 --> 00:26:48,350
Morning, Sir.

539
00:26:51,980 --> 00:26:54,020
Duan Tuizhi is investigating Mrs. Chen.

540
00:26:54,020 --> 00:26:56,340
Just because of what happened
at Power Company Guesthouse?

541
00:26:56,340 --> 00:26:59,000
At that time,
she claimed to be my wife's friend.

542
00:26:59,110 --> 00:27:01,810
If the investigation continues,
her cover will be blown soon.

543
00:27:01,810 --> 00:27:03,030
So we must send her back.

544
00:27:03,030 --> 00:27:04,510
Get her the exit permit
as soon as possible.

545
00:27:04,510 --> 00:27:05,970
Alright. I'll do it today.

